After the huge success of last year, the Belgium Festival was back, again. The week-long celebrations featured beer, wine and chocolate tasting and pairing workshops, in addition to the delicious culinary dinners hosted at Nairobi Serena. Visiting chef Olivier Brucknerprepared threeculinary dinnersat the hotel, adding a touch of Belgian culinary flavours to Kenyan ingredients. On top of that, beer sommelier Jean Hummler, owner of Brussels&rsquo; famous bar &ldquo;Moeder Lambic&rdquo;, gave the Belgian Week an extra Belgian twist during the three days of Belgian beer-tasting workshops.In attendance were Tourism CS Najib Balala and Belgium Ambassador Roxane de Bilderling, among other dignitaries and guests.